The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 19 January is 174,277 (20,086.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 14 January, there were 7,044 new confirmed cases (811.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 07 January, there were 11,213 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 37% (4,169 fewer cases).
